    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - ENGINE SYMPTOMS DIAGNOSTICS - Description</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Description</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <para>Diagnostic test procedures help technicians find problems systematically and quickly to avoid
                unnecessary repairs. In this section, the concern is known and diagnostics are used to identify the
                cause of the complaint.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, make
                        sure the transmission is in neutral, parking brake is set, and wheels are blocked before doing
                        service bay diagnostics on engine or vehicle.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
